INSERT INTO `draft_chapters` VALUES (1,1,9,8,'Draft: Bob and Jake uncover the mastermind behind the plot...\ndraft testing','2025-04-02 04:00:00','2025-06-05 20:19:05'),(2,1,7,9,'Draft: A new clue emerges from the old diary...','2025-04-02 05:00:00','2025-04-02 05:00:00'),(3,2,4,5,'Draft: Emma learns the crystal’s true origin...','2025-04-02 06:00:00','2025-04-02 06:00:00'),(4,2,5,6,'Draft: The guardian reveals a hidden prophecy...','2025-04-02 07:00:00','2025-04-02 07:00:00'),(11,30,26,1,'draft testing','2025-06-04 21:47:16','2025-06-04 21:47:16'),(15,33,24,1,'fetch draft testing','2025-06-09 19:49:37','2025-06-09 19:49:37'),(18,34,24,1,'chapter 1 draft testing','2025-06-11 10:25:37','2025-06-11 10:25:37'),(19,35,24,1,'w draft','2025-06-11 10:28:03','2025-06-11 10:28:03'),(20,37,24,3,'moon 3','2025-06-11 19:21:00','2025-06-11 19:21:00'),(26,41,24,4,'4','2025-06-12 14:42:14','2025-06-12 14:45:15'),(30,42,27,3,'chapter 3 draft','2025-06-13 15:06:35','2025-06-13 15:06:35'),(32,43,27,4,'secord c4 draft','2025-06-13 15:12:39','2025-06-13 15:12:39'),(33,44,27,3,'third c33','2025-06-13 15:32:24','2025-06-13 15:32:49'),(35,44,27,4,'third c4 draft','2025-06-13 15:33:27','2025-06-13 15:33:27'),(37,44,27,6,'third c6','2025-06-13 15:47:49','2025-06-13 15:47:49'),(40,46,27,4,'Fi c4 draft','2025-06-13 16:01:36','2025-06-13 16:01:36'),(41,45,27,4,'fi c4 draft','2025-06-13 16:03:24','2025-06-13 16:03:24'),(45,41,24,5,'field c5 draft','2025-06-14 10:05:45','2025-06-14 10:05:45'),(46,48,24,3,'no cover 2 draft','2025-06-14 10:32:47','2025-06-14 10:32:47'),(47,49,24,2,'no cover 3 c2','2025-06-14 10:47:27','2025-06-14 10:47:27'),(48,50,24,5,'nc c5 draft update','2025-06-14 11:27:44','2025-06-14 11:28:14'),(51,51,26,3,'w1 c3 draft','2025-06-14 11:41:03','2025-06-14 11:41:03'),(52,51,26,5,'w1 draft 5','2025-06-14 11:44:33','2025-06-14 11:44:33'),(53,51,26,6,'white draft 6','2025-06-14 11:44:49','2025-06-14 11:45:34'),(55,52,27,3,'black c3 draft','2025-06-14 12:01:50','2025-06-14 12:01:50'),(57,53,27,2,'black 2 draft','2025-06-14 12:03:53','2025-06-14 12:03:53'),(58,54,24,5,'The New Resident\n---------------------------------------\nWeeks passed. Room Five was sealed again.\n\nUntil the new student, Alex, arrived.\n\nHe heard about the stories, the disappearances, and the rumors. But he didn’t care. He liked danger. He liked breaking rules.\n\nOne night, he wandered the halls. He found the door. It looked just like any other now. Fresh paint. New lock. But something about it pulled at him.\n\nAs he leaned close, he heard it—barely audible, a girl’s voice:\n\n“Help me…”\n\nHe reached for the knob.\n\nBehind the door, in the mirror, Lena smiled.\n\nSo did the others.','2025-06-28 19:58:03','2025-06-28 19:58:03'),(59,55,26,3,'The Final Winding\n--------------------------------------\nThe next day, the shop was quiet—too quiet. Evelyn stepped into the ticking room, but the clocks were silent. The golden watch sat alone on the table. Beside it was a note in elegant handwriting:\n\n“Your time has come to choose.”\n\nShe hesitated, then picked up the watch. It ticked once.\n\nThe world changed again. Now she stood in a peaceful park, the sun warm on her skin. A little boy ran toward her, arms outstretched. “Mama!” he cried joyfully.\n\nTears welled in her eyes. The boy looked just like her childhood photos. A man stood nearby, smiling warmly. Evelyn felt it—not fear, but peace.\n\nBack in the shop, the clocks remained still. She placed the watch back on the table and smiled.\n\nThe future wasn\'t something to fear. It was something to meet with open arms.\n\nThe clockmaker was gone, but his lesson remained: Time doesn’t trap us—it reveals who we’re meant to be.','2025-06-29 21:30:20','2025-06-29 21:30:20'),(60,56,24,5,'Signal Terminated\n----------------------------------\nWeeks passed. Jared and Mia changed identities, moved countries, erased digital traces.\n\nBut one night, a familiar static crackled from an old hotel radio.\n\n“Delta-7… Sierra-1… Terminate.”\n\nJared smashed the radio.\n\nSomehow, they were still being tracked.\n\nBut this time, they were ready.\n\nMia slid a new device onto the table. “We’ll send our own message. Flip the target. Make them run.”\n\nJared nodded, eyes fierce.\n\n“The hunters become the hunted.”\n\nAnd as the screen lit up, a new signal was born — one that would end the silence for good.','2025-06-29 21:39:17','2025-06-29 21:39:17'),(62,58,26,4,'The Eclipse and the Starcall \n------------------------------------\nAtop the Celestial Spire, the sky turned violet. The eclipse had begun. Liora placed the vial into the Starwell. The earth trembled. The Spire sang in a thousand voices. The darkness, enraged, rose for one final strike. Shadows swirled into a beast of despair, roaring, “You are too young. Too weak.” But Liora stood firm. “I am not alone.” She drew on the grove, the dragon’s wind, Caelen’s fire, and her own soul. Moonlight burst from her hands, not white but silver-gold. The beast screamed, dissolving like smoke in morning light. The stars blinked—then shimmered brighter. The grove’s magic pulsed across the land, waking the world. Trees whispered her name not as a girl, but as Guardian. Caelen vanished, his task complete, leaving behind a trail of falling stars. Liora looked to the sky, her Moonmark now glowing forever. The Starlight Grove was reborn—and so was she.jjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjjj','2025-06-29 23:29:57','2025-06-30 05:08:12'),(63,59,34,3,'r','2025-06-30 03:30:59','2025-06-30 03:30:59'),(65,60,26,2,'jjjjjjjjjjjjj','2025-06-30 05:18:53','2025-06-30 05:18:53'),(67,62,24,3,'That night, Talia fled the citadel. Guards chased her, blades drawn, torches lighting the night.\n\nBut she wasn’t alone.\n\nThe butterfly grew large—almost the size of a hawk—and shielded her with glowing wings as they entered the Moonshade Forest, a place said to devour all who enter.\n\nBut the forest welcomed her.\n\nOld spirits whispered her name.\n\nA path of floating blossoms appeared beneath her feet.\n\nShe walked until the trees parted—and there stood a silver gate, woven from vines and memory.\n\nThe butterfly landed on her shoulder.\n\n“This is where you begin again.”','2025-07-12 19:52:54','2025-07-12 19:52:54');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `draft_chapters` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

